The paper deals with the complexity of constraint satisfaction problems, which is a fundamental topic in theoretical computer science. The focus on parameterized complexity and the use of size constraints suggest that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely categories. The use of constraint languages and relations suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as possible categories. Finally, the study of special cases such as Independent Set and Biclique suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a possible category.
